<paragraph id="8BF136C48948FFECFF068AA3C107FEA2" blockId="78.[151,1436,216,431]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<materialsCitation id="3B263C998948FFECFF068AA3C103FEA2" accessionNumber="ZMB 85623" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Sri Lanka" location="Pareiss" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" specimenCode="ZMB 2493" specimenCount="1">
Referred specimen (marked with 
<typeStatus id="54F588668948FFECFD968AA3C06DFF42" box="[519,565,216,239]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">type</typeStatus>
*): 
<specimenCode id="DBE89EBF8948FFECFDF78AA3C0B9FF42" box="[614,737,216,239]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB 2493</specimenCode>
, body in alcohol and 
<accessionNumber id="941DAB278948FFECFC458AA3C604FF42" box="[980,1116,216,239]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/ZMB85623" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<collectionCode id="ED5FAE018948FFECFC458AA3C656FF42" box="[980,1038,216,239]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
85623
</accessionNumber>
, skull and skeleton [of 
<specimenCode id="DBE89EBF8948FFECFAF38AA3C35AFEA2" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB 2493</specimenCode>
]; 
<collectingCountry id="F35976548948FFECFE828A83C327FEA2" box="[275,383,248,271]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
; collector unknown; purchased from 
<location id="8E91601F8948FFECFC9D8A83C103FEA2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E787D2894BFFECFF068DE3C3A2FE02:8E91601F8948FFECFC9D8A83C103FEA2" box="[780,859,248,271]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Pareiss" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Pareiss</location>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136C48948FFECFF068B63C3A2FE02" blockId="78.[151,1436,216,431]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<materialsCitation id="3B263C998948FFECFF068B63C3ADFE82" box="[151,501,279,303]" collectionCode="ZMB" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" specimenCode="ZMB 2493" specimenCount="1">
Comment: Although 
<specimenCode id="DBE89EBF8948FFECFEEF8B63C3ADFE82" box="[382,501,280,303]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB 2493</specimenCode>
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B263C998948FFECFE6F8B63C3BAFEC2" collectionCode="BMNH" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" specimenCode="BMNH 1852.1" specimenCount="1">
is erroneously listed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D478948FFECFD6E8B63C63EFE82" authority="Templetoni Fitzinger" authorityName="Templetoni Fitzinger" authorityYear="1855" box="[767,1126,280,303]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Phyllorhina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD68948FFECFD6E8B63C1A4FE82" box="[767,1020,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Phyllorhina Templetoni</emphasis>
Fitzinger
</taxonomicName>
, it was described by Kelaart (1850), who appears to have based the description on several specimens. Tate (1941b: 390) mentioned two “cotypes”: 
<specimenCode id="DBE89EBF8948FFECFED18B23C3BAFEC2" box="[320,482,344,367]" collectionCode="BMNH" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">BMNH 1852.1</specimenCode>
</materialsCitation>
. 
<materialsCitation id="3B263C998948FFECFE778B23C1C0FEC2" box="[486,920,344,367]" collectionCode="ZMB" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" specimenCode="ZMB 2493" specimenCount="1">
24.2 and 1852.1.24.4. Since 
<specimenCode id="DBE89EBF8948FFECFCB18B23C1C0FEC2" box="[800,920,344,367]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB 2493</specimenCode>
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B263C998948FFECFC308B23C632FE22" collectionCode="ZMB" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" specimenCount="2">
was purchased from Pareiss it is very doubtful that it was part of the 
<typeStatus id="54F588668948FFECFE218B03C386FE22" box="[432,478,376,399]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">type</typeStatus>
series, and hence should not be considered a 
<typeStatus id="54F588668948FFECFC558B03C1ADFE22" box="[964,1013,376,399]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">type</typeStatus>
. The 
<collectionCode id="ED5FAE018948FFECFBA18B03C632FE22" box="[1072,1130,376,399]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="3B263C998948FFECFBE18B03C3AEFE02" collectionCode="ZMB" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" specimenCode="ZMB 2443" specimenCount="1">
specimen tag is also inaccurately labelled “ 
<specimenCode id="DBE89EBF8948FFECFEFE8BE3C3B4FE02" box="[367,492,408,431]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="Museum">ZMB 2443</specimenCode>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
